50|$|A {{week after}} the end of the siege, Owsley was {{contacted}} by special agent Joseph DiZinno from the Forensic Science Research and Training Center at the FBI Academy in Quantico. On behalf of Danny Greathouse, chief of the FBI's Disaster Unit, who was overseeing the situation at Waco, DiZinno requested Owsley's and Douglas H. Ubelaker's assistance in identifying the victims from inside <b>the</b> <b>Branch</b> <b>Davidian</b> <b>compound.</b>|$|E
50|$|Sessions was FBI {{director}} {{during the}} controversial 1992 confrontation at Ruby Ridge, Idaho, {{at which the}} unarmed Vicky Weaver was shot dead by an FBI sniper. This incident provoked heavy criticism of the Bureau, as did the deadly assault on <b>the</b> <b>Branch</b> <b>Davidian</b> <b>compound</b> at Waco which lasted from February 28 to April 19, 1993. These incidents were also related {{to the discovery of}} severe procedural shortcomings at the FBI's crime laboratory.|$|E
