50|$|The {{events at}} Waco spurred both {{criminal}} prosecution and civil litigation. On August 3, 1993, {{a federal grand}} jury returned a superseding ten-count indictment against 12 of <b>the</b> surviving <b>Branch</b> <b>Davidians.</b> <b>The</b> grand jury charged, among other things, that <b>the</b> <b>Branch</b> <b>Davidians</b> had conspired to, and aided and abetted in, murder of federal officers, and had unlawfully possessed and used various firearms. The government dismissed the charges against one of <b>the</b> 12 <b>Branch</b> <b>Davidians</b> pursuant to a plea bargain.|$|R
