50|$|Despite being {{informed}} that <b>the</b> <b>Branch</b> <b>Davidians</b> knew a raid was coming, the ATF commander ordered that the raid go ahead, {{even though their}} plan depended on reaching <b>the</b> <b>compound</b> without <b>the</b> <b>Branch</b> <b>Davidians</b> being armed and prepared. While not standard procedure, ATF agents had their blood type written on their arms or neck after leaving the staging area and before the raid, because it was recommended by the military to facilitate speedy blood transfusions {{in the case of}} injury.|$|R
